    "body": "More log: `future block slot=186047 currentSlot=186046 now=1595666368400 state.genesisTime=1593433805`\r\nThe explorer https://altona.beaconcha.in/block/186047 shows a time of 1595666369000, it's 600ms clock disparity while the spec allows a 500ms disparity.\r\nAlso, I found that this validation in gossip block needs to be modified\r\n```\r\nif (signedBlock.message.slot * milliSecPerSlot >\r\n        getCurrentSlot(this.config, state.genesisTime) * milliSecPerSlot + MAXIMUM_GOSSIP_CLOCK_DISPARITY) {\r\n      // console.log(`@@@ !!! future block slot=${slot} currentSlot=${getCurrentSlot(this.config, state.genesisTime)} now=${Date.now()} state.genesisTime=${state.genesisTime}`);\r\n      return ExtendedValidatorResult.ignore;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nWe need to be able to pass in (now + MAXIMUM_GOSSIP_CLOCK_DISPARITY) when `getCurrentSlot`, probably create another version of it. The current validation makes no sense in terms of clock disparity.\r\nSo with this example, it still fail but we will eventually can validate it after 100ms more (note that we receive multiple duplicate gossip block if it's invalid - hope we receive them at different timestamp)\r\nSo the gossip message cache should not be changed, only cache the valid ones, let's invalid one another try at later timestamp.",
